properties.areaDesc: Lake Michigan from Seul Choix Point to Rock Island Passage 5NM offshore to Mid Lake; Lake Michigan South of a line from Seul Choix Point to the Mackinac Bridge and North of a line from Charlevoix MI to South Fox Island 5NM offshore; Lake Michigan from Charlevoix to Point Betsie MI 5NM Offshore to mid lake; Lake Michigan from Rock Island Passage to Sturgeon Bay WI 5NM offshore to mid lake
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 17 at 9:03AM CST until January 18 at 9:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, southeast winds 15 to 25 kt with
gusts up to 35 kt and waves 4 to 7 feet expected. For the Gale
Watch, northwest winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 35 kt and
waves 4 to 7 feet possible.

* WHERE...North third of Lake Michigan, north of a line from
Sturgeon Bay to Point Betsie.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from midnight tonight to 9 AM CST
Saturday. For the Gale Watch, from Saturday evening through
late Saturday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 9 AM CST SATURDAY... ...GALE WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY EVENING THROUGH LATE SATURDAY NIGHT
